            "value": "persistentslab",
            "display": "Persistent slab"
          },
          "comment": "<p>Two persistent weak layers are buried down ~100 and ~130 cm. Last weeks snow, combined with extreme winds, overloaded these layers triggering large, destructive avalanches. Be very suspect of slopes that haven't recently avalanched. These weak layers are still within human triggering depths.</p><p></p>",
