          "width": 2142,
          "height": 2856,
          "credit": "Parks Canada",
          "caption": "<p>Size 3 avalanche that propagated on the Jan 26th surface hoar layer, down 100-150cm. This one in the photo was naturally triggered 24-48 hours ago. Explosive hand charge testing 200m away triggered two sz 3 avalanches, both on the Jan 26 surface hoar. One of these was remote triggered from 50m away.</p>",
          "tag": "avalanche",
          "isArchived": false,
          "altText": "Parks Canada Mountain Safety staff examining fracture line of sz 3 avalanche on Roundhill Ridge",
          "dateTaken": "2026-03-03T23:30:17.835Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "774f8df4-2d4d-490c-9dd2-d95fe2c5dc8a",
          "url": "http://res.cloudinary.com/forecasts/image/upload/v1772580889/prod/parks/glacier/djmhtuc270kl0bwtn15b.jpg",
          "width": 2856,
          "height": 2142,
          "credit": "Parks Canada",
          "caption": "<p>These large blocks of avalanche debris are on slopes less than 20 degrees. This size 3 avalanche was naturally triggered in the last 24-48hrs on a N-facing slope, pulling well-back onto low angle slopes in the Mt Fidelity prohibited zone. The failure plane is the Jan 26th surface hoar, down 1-1.5m</p>",
          "tag": "avalanche",
          "isArchived": false,
          "altText": "Large blocks of avalanche debris on low angle slopes, too low angle to slide.",
          "dateTaken": "2026-03-03T23:34:56.255Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "a7c1ba2b-4997-4d81-a88f-2ebadef9c47f",
          "url": "http://res.cloudinary.com/forecasts/image/upload/v1772490455/prod/parks/glacier/czhe9xc2vo36efri1hnb.jpg",
          "width": 5000,
          "height": 3746,
          "credit": "Parks Canada",
          "caption": "<p>Naturally triggered size 4 avalanche from Grizzly Mountain. Ran full path, across creek, and several dozen metres up the other side of the valley. Of note, the slide jumped the gully wall halfway down and logged some mature timber on the right side of the picture.</p><p>Frequent Flyer, the avalanche path to the left, did not produce a large avalanche during this last cycle. It should be a primary concern for anyone skiing up Connaught Creek in the next few days</p>",
          "tag": "avalanche",
          "isArchived": false,
          "altText": "Naturally triggered size 4 avalanche off Grizzly Mountain",
          "dateTaken": "2026-03-02T22:27:42.069Z"
        }
      ]
